'I found a bear by the stream,' said the minister, 'and preached God's holy word. The bear was so mesmerized that he let me baptize him.' Jokes.JokeTxt: Researchers for the Massachusetts Turnpike recently found 200 dead crows and there was an immediate concern about Avian Flu. A pathologist examined the crows and found the cause of death to be vehicular impacts. They then determined that 98% of the vehicles were trucks, and only 2% were cars. They then hired an Ornithological Behaviorist to determine the cause of that disproportionate percentage, and he quickly determined the cause. When crows eat road kill, they always have a look-out crow in a nearby tree to warn of danger. They discovered that while all the lookout crows could shout 'Cah!', not a single one could shout 'Truck!'

Jokes.JokeTxt: WILY'S LAW: n. The only known exception to Newton's Law of Gravity, Wily's Law states that an animal or person can suspend himself in midair provided (a) he is in a cartoon, and (b) he doesn't look down and realize he is no longer on solid ground.
